// MongoDB Start From here

Model the following Library information system as a graph model,and answer 
the following queries using Cypher.
Consider a library information system having different types of books like text,
reference, bibliography etc. A student can buy one or more types of book. A
student can recommend or rate a book according to its type.

1. Identify the labels and relationships, along with their properties, and draw a high-level Graph model. 

2. Create nodes and relationships, along with their properties, and
visualize your actual Graph model. 

CREATE
(b1:Book {title:'Mathematics 101', type:'Text', author:'R. Kumar'}),
(b2:Book {title:'Physics Handbook', type:'Reference', author:'S. Sharma'}),
(b3:Book {title:'History Guide', type:'Bibliography', author:'A. Singh'}),
(b4:Book {title:'Chemistry Basics', type:'Text', author:'M. Verma'}),
(b5:Book {title:'Biology Reference', type:'Reference', author:'P. Desai'}),

(s1:Student {name:'Amresh'}),
(s2:Student {name:'Mitesh'}),
(s3:Student {name:'Shubham'}),

(s1)-[:BOUGHT]->(b1),
(s1)-[:BOUGHT]->(b2),
(s2)-[:BOUGHT]->(b3),
(s2)-[:BOUGHT]->(b4),
(s3)-[:BOUGHT]->(b1),
(s3)-[:BOUGHT]->(b5),

(s1)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(b1),
(s2)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(b4),
(s3)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(b5),

(s1)-[:RATED {rating:5}]->(b1),
(s2)-[:RATED {rating:4}]->(b4),
(s3)-[:RATED {rating:5}]->(b5);

3. Answer the following Queries :

a. List the books of type “text”
MATCH (b:Book {type:'Text'})
RETURN b.title, b.author;

b. List the name of student who bought a text and reference types books.
MATCH (s:Student)-[:BOUGHT]->(b:Book)
WITH s, collect(DISTINCT b.type) AS types
WHERE 'Text' IN types AND 'Reference' IN types
RETURN s.name, types;

c. List the most recommended book type.
MATCH (s:Student)-[:RECOMMENDED]->(b:Book)
RETURN b.type, count(s) AS Recommendations
ORDER BY Recommendations DESC
LIMIT 1;

d. List the student who buy more than one type of book
MATCH (s:Student)-[:BOUGHT]->(b:Book)
WITH s, count(DISTINCT b.type) AS TypeCount
WHERE TypeCount > 1
RETURN s.name, TypeCount;
